2C%20was%20conscience-keeper%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%20to%20the%20bar%20and%20the%20bench%20alike%2C%20to%20the%20various%20state%20governments%20he%20had%20represented%20over%20the%20decades%2C%20and%20even%20to%20the%20nation.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20just%2046%20when%2C%20having%20represented%20the%20Union%20government%20as%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20from%201972%20to%201975%2C%20he%20was%20faced%20with%20the%20imposition%20of%20the%20Emergency%20on%20June%2025%2C%201975.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFali%20refused%20to%20stand%20by%20and%20defend%20this%20suspension%20of%20constitutional%20rights.%20He%20promptly%20resigned.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judges%20had%20folded%20up%20like%20a%20defeated%20pack%20of%20cards%2C%20this%20doughty%20young%20lawyer%20stood%20up%20and%20was%20counted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20another%20time%2C%20much%20later%2C%20Fali%20returned%20the%20brief%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20in%20the%20prestigious%20Narmada%20Dam%20rehabilitation%20case%2C%20when%20he%20learnt%20that%20the%20same%20government%20was%20looking%20the%20other%20way%20as%20Christian%20tribals%20were%20being%20attacked%20in%20the%20Dang%20district%2C%20their%20churches%20burnt%2C%20and%20their%20bibles%20desecrated.%20Fali%20first%20tried%20to%20prevail%20upon%20the%20minister%20who%20briefed%20him%20to%20ensure%20government%20intervention%20and%20protection%20of%20the%20hapless%20minority.%20But%20when%20he%20found%20that%20Christian%20tribals%20were%20being%20attacked%20and%20killed%20despite%20assurances%20by%20the%20minister%2C%20he%20refused%20to%20appear%20for%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20equally%20questioning%20of%20himself%20and%20the%20role%20he%20unwittingly%20played%20in%20certain%20cases.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffali-nariman-obituary-indira-jaising%5C%22%3EAt%20a%20Time%20When%20the%20Battles%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Future%20Will%20Be%20Fought%20in%20its%20Courts%2C%20We%20Will%20Miss%20Fali%20Nariman%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20successfully%20defended%20the%20Union%20Carbide%20Corporation%20and%20its%20American%20directors%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Bhopal%20gas%20disaster%2C%20and%20having%20brought%20a%20modicum%20of%20closure%20to%20the%20legal%20battles%20through%20the%20%24470%20million%20settlement%20that%20he%20helped%20negotiate%20before%20getting%20the%20imprimatur%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Fali%20was%20later%20anguished%20by%20the%20enormous%20human%20tragedy%20that%20Carbide%20had%20inflicted.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202010%2C%20he%20asked%20me%20to%20represent%20his%20close%20friend%2C%20the%20former%20managing%20director%20of%20UCC%20India%2C%20in%20a%20curative%20petition%20initiated%20by%20the%20then%20Attorney%20General%20for%20India.%20And%20when%20I%20asked%20him%20whether%20he%20would%20lead%20me%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20his%20answer%20was%20a%20deeply%20disturbed%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%E2%80%99t%2C%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20tortured%20by%20it%E2%80%9D.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20years%20later%20Fali%20devoted%20a%20lengthy%20chapter%20to%20this%20anguish%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadm-jabalpur-emergency-niren-de-tushar-mehta%5C%22%3Ehis%20memoir%2C%20%3Cem%3EBefore%20Memory%20Fades%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELess%20disturbed%20but%20nonetheless%20keenly%20aware%20that%20perhaps%20he%20had%20been%20instrumental%20in%20bringing%20about%20a%20less-than-perfect%20system%20for%20the%20selection%20of%20judges%2C%20Fali%20always%20wondered%20how%20things%20might%20have%20turned%20out%20if%20he%20had%20not%20been%20as%20successful%20in%20arguing%20the%20first%20and%20second%20Judges%20cases%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1294854%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ES.P.%20Gupta%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F753224%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3ESupreme%20Court%20Advocates%20on%20Record%20Association%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20cases%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcollegium-system-judges-knockout-blow%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98collegium%E2%80%99%20system%20of%20judicial%20appointments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20giving%20India%20the%20unique%20distinction%20of%20being%20the%20only%20major%20nation%20where%20judges%20select%20future%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20later%20years%2C%20Fali%20continued%20as%20conscience%20keeper%20through%20his%20calmly%20reasoned%2C%20gentle%2C%20yet%20persuasive%20reminders%20of%20the%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%20of%20our%20judicial%20system.%20Putting%20pen%20to%20paper%20time%20and%20again%20during%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20he%20wrote%20%3Cem%3EThe%20State%20of%20the%20Nation%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2013)%2C%20%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Legal%20System%20%E2%80%93%20Can%20it%20be%20Saved%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017)%2C%20%3Cem%3EGod%20Save%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2018)%2C%20%3Cem%3EHarmony%20Amidst%20Disharmony%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%2C%20and%20even%20the%20very%20recent%20guide%20for%20citizens%2C%20%3Cem%3EYou%20Must%20Know%20Your%20Constitution%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2023).%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20of%20course%2C%20on%20another%20and%20more%20personal%20note%2C%20he%20most%20recently%20co-authored%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Delightful%20Mr.%20Daphtary%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0on%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20Solicitor%20General%2C%20C.K.%20Daphtary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20will%20be%20written%20on%20this%20great%20jurist%E2%80%99s%20contributions%20to%20the%20bar%2C%20the%20bench%2C%20and%20the%20nation.%20But%20to%20me%2C%20Fali%20will%20always%20remain%20the%20conscience%20keeper.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERest%20in%20peace%2C%20Fali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EChander%20Uday%20Singh%20is%20a%20Senior%20Advocate.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708520427000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F21181850%2FUntitled-design-3-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffali-nariman-conscience-keeper-obituary%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Through%20his%20career%2C%20he%20has%20played%20this%20role%20through%20his%20calmly%20reasoned%2C%20gentle%2C%20yet%20persuasive%20reminders%20of%20the%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%20of%20our%20judicial%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffali-nariman-conscience-keeper-obituary%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Heavy%20snow%20blankets%20parts%20of%20China%2C%20emergency%20measures%20implemented%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708520396000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107888054%2Cimgsize-658916.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fsnowfall-in-china-emergency-measures-heavy-snow-beijing-casualty-death%2Fphotostory%2F107888054.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107888054.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%E2%80%8BHeavy%20snow%20blankets%20parts%20of%20China%2C%20emergency%20measures%20implemented%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fsnowfall-in-china-emergency-measures-heavy-snow-beijing-casualty-death%2Fphotostory%2F107888054.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fsnowfall-in-china-emergency-measures-heavy-snow-beijing-casualty-death%2Famp_etphotostory%2F107888054.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fsnowfall-in-china-emergency-measures-heavy-snow-beijing-casualty-death%2Famp_etphotostory%2F107888054.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Russia%20Has%20Never%20Hurt%20India%20Interests'%3A%20Jaishankar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F29133605%2FFzuFHifXoAIWH-o.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20External%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20has%20said%20of%20the%20Indo-Russian%20relations%20that%20as%20far%20as%20independent%20India%20was%20concerned%2C%20%E2%80%9CRussia%20has%20never%20hurt%20our%20interests%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20when%20asked%20by%20the%20German%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EHandelsblatt%3C%2Fem%3E%20if%20India%E2%80%99s%20purchase%20of%20Russian%20oil%20was%20a%20burden%20on%20its%20relationship%20with%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEveryone%20conducts%20a%20relationship%20based%20on%20their%20past%20experiences.%20If%20I%20look%20at%20the%20history%20of%20India%20post-independence%2C%20Russia%20has%20never%20hurt%20our%20interests%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20relations%20of%20powers%20like%20Europe%2C%20the%20US%2C%20China%20or%20Japan%20with%20Russia%2C%20they%20have%20all%20seen%20ups%20and%20downs.%20We%20have%20had%20a%20stable%20and%20always%20very%20friendly%20relationship%20with%20Russia.%20And%20our%20relationship%20with%20Russia%20today%20is%20based%20on%20this%20experience.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Findias-import-dependency-on-oil-and-gas-to-surpass-80-by-fy28%2Farticle67154624.ece%5C%22%3Edependent%20on%20oil%20imports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20its%20domestic%20oil%20output%20lags%20behind%20growing%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20purchased%20oil%20from%20Russia%20at%20cheaper%20prices%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20cut%20its%20oil%20import%20bill%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20discounted%20prices%20owing%20to%20Western%20sanctions%20starting%20in%20early%202022%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-russian-oil-jaishankar-sergei-lavrov%5C%22%3Edefended%20its%20decision%20to%20defy%20the%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20arguing%20it%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20lower%20prices%20whenever%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20reiterated%20this%20stance%20in%20his%20interview%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHandelsblatt%3C%2Fem%3E%20when%20asked%20if%20India%20and%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20differing%20relations%20with%20Russia%20%E2%80%9Cput%20a%20strain%20on%20India-Europe%20relations%E2%80%9D.%20The%20interview%20was%20conducted%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%20he%20attended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20mentioned%20the%20energy%20issue.%20When%20the%20fighting%20started%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Europe%20shifted%20a%20large%20part%20of%20its%20energy%20procurement%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%20%E2%80%93%20until%20then%20the%20main%20supplier%20for%20India%20and%20other%20countries.%20What%20should%20we%20have%20done%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20cases%2C%20our%20Middle%20East%20suppliers%20gave%20priority%20to%20Europe%20because%20Europe%20paid%20higher%20prices.%20Either%20we%20would%20have%20had%20no%20energy%20because%20everything%20would%20have%20gone%20to%20them.%20Or%20we%20would%20have%20ended%20up%20paying%20a%20lot%20more%20because%20you%20were%20paying%20more%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20global%20order%20is%20currently%20facing%20%E2%80%9Cmultiple%20kinds%20of%20stress%E2%80%9D.%20The%20stress%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshocks%E2%80%9D%20such%20as%20Covid%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20NATO%20withdrawal%20from%20Afghanistan%20and%20disruptive%20climate%20events%20that%20are%20happening%20more%20and%20more%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20about%20strengthening%20the%20international%20order%2C%20but%20also%20about%20changing%20this%20order.%20Who%20shapes%20it%20and%20on%20what%20basis%3F%20The%20international%20order%20must%20evolve%20further%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20proposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20it%20further%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CTake%20the%20United%20Nations%20as%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20international%20order.%20The%20UN%20started%20with%2050%20members%2C%20now%20it%20has%20almost%20200%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20management%20of%20the%20UN%20has%20not%20changed.%20The%20group%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20top%2020%20or%2030%20economies%20has%20changed%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades.%20Ten%20years%20ago%2C%20India%20was%20the%20eleventh%20largest%20economy%2C%20now%20we%20are%20number%20five.%20In%20a%20few%20years%2C%20we%20will%20be%20the%20third%20largest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20reiterating%20his%20stance%20on%20the%20need%20for%20reforms%20at%20the%20UN%2C%20he%20said%20the%20countries%20blocking%20the%20reform%20are%20those%20which%20are%20%E2%80%9Cin%20denial%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20way%20the%20world%20has%20changed%20in%20recent%20decades.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20real%20issue%20is%3A%20how%20do%20we%20refresh%20the%20international%20order%2C%20how%20do%20we%20renovate%20and%20reform%20it%20and%20its%20institutions%3F%20There%20is%20no%20point%20in%20saying%20to%20international%20institutions%3A%20%E2%80%98Do%20your%20job%20better%E2%80%99%20if%20they%20are%20not%20capable%20of%20doing%20so.%20Look%20at%20how%20the%20international%20order%20simply%20collapsed%20during%20a%20historically%20large%20problem%20like%20Covid.%20Every%20country%20acted%20in%20its%20best%20interest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20being%20asked%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20change%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20German%20policy%20given%20that%20India%20is%20trying%20to%20buy%20more%20weapons%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20Germany%20has%20long%20been%20cautious%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20security%20and%20defense.%20In%20contrast%2C%20we%20have%20had%20robust%20cooperation%20with%20France%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20to%20a%20more%20limited%20extent%20with%20Spain%20and%20Italy.%20But%20I%20have%20seen%20a%20development%20in%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20in%20recent%20years%3B%20my%20interlocutors%20now%20understand%20that%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20completely%20exclude%20one%20part%20of%20a%20relationship.%20It%20is%20developing%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20is%20good%20for%20both%20sides.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708518567000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F29133605%2FFzuFHifXoAIWH-o.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frussia-has-never-hurt-india-interests-jaishankar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Speaking%20to%20German%20newspaper%20Handelsblatt%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%2C%20the%20external%20affairs%20minister%20defended%20India's%20decision%20to%20buy%20Russian%20oil%20amid%20Western%20sanctions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frussia-has-never-hurt-india-interests-jaishankar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sunset%20video%20shows%20Mexico%20volcano%20spewing%20ash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708518450000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fic