ay%2C%C2%A0would%20just%20collapse%2C%20Jensehaugen%20told%3Cem%3E%20DW%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20no%20schools%2C%20no%20healthcare%2C%20no%20social%20benefits%20for%20those%20in%20need.%20Add%20that%20to%20the%20context%20of%20a%20collapsing%20state%2C%20and%20it%20has%20ramifications%20outside%20the%20camps%20as%20well%20because%20people%20will%20need%20to%20go%20elsewhere%20to%20get%2C%20well%2C%20anything.%20That%20would%20put%20an%20extreme%20strain%20on%20local%20society.%20Besides%20demonstrations%20or%20riots%20in%20the%20camps%2C%20you%20might%20also%20get%20more%20people%20joining%20criminal%20gangs%20or%20militant%20organizations%2C%20just%20for%20the%20salary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fjordan%2Ft-39527586%5C%22%3EJordan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20slightly%20better%2C%20as%20the%20state%20could%20potentially%20replace%20some%20of%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20services.%20However%20because%20of%20the%C2%A0sensitivities%20around%20UNRWA%2C%20Jordanian%20leadership%20may%20be%20unwilling%2C%20analysts%20argue.%C2%A0Jordan%2C%C2%A0like%20other%20Arab%20nations%2C%20has%C2%A0no%C2%A0desire%20to%C2%A0be%20seen%20as%20supporting%20attacks%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgency%20for%20stability%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20impact%20will%20differ%20from%20country%20to%20country%2C%20Hiltermann%20agreed.%20%E2%80%9CBut%2C%20given%20the%20highly%20volatile%C2%A0environment%20for%20refugees%C2%A0there%2C%20the%20political%20impact%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20worst%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%20There%20is%20a%20reason%20why%20the%20Israeli%20military%20would%20like%20UNRWA%20to%20remain%20fully%20funded%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jensehaugen%20and%20fellow%20researchers%20were%20interviewing%20donor%20countries%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmi.no%2Fpublications%2F8574-unrwa-funding-crisis-and-the-way-forward%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20a%202022%20study%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202022%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20topic%20of%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20funding%20struggles%2C%C2%A0the%20agency%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpalestinian-refugees-unrwa-collapse-us-aid%2Fa-55660557%5C%22%3Elong%20run%20a%20deficit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20found%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20so-called%20stability%20argument%E2%80%9D%20to%20have%20been%20a%20key%20motivator%20for%20donor%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20funding%20UNRWA%20is%20a%20cheap%20way%20of%20securing%20stability%20in%20the%20region%20because%20it%20means%20that%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20children%20get%20educated%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jensehaugen%20explained%2C%20noting%20that%20poverty%20and%20lack%20of%20education%20are%20proven%20drivers%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fiiss-military-think-tank-says-more-dangerous-decade-likely%2Fa-68243699%5C%22%3Eextremism%20and%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20really%20huge%20paradox%20now%20with%20constraining%20funding%20for%20UNRWA%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jensehaugen%20continued.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20potential%20for%20instability%20is%20so%20clear%20and%20donors%20already%20know%20it%20can%20get%20worse.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20observers%20say%20that%20European%20governments%20are%20well%20aware%20that%20if%20UNRWA%20fails%2C%20they%20could%20see%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20irregular%20migration%20from%20Lebanon%20and%20Jordan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUNRWA%E2%80%99s%20collapse%20would%20be%20dangerous%20for%20local%20stability%20in%20each%20location%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Crisis%20Group%E2%80%99s%20Hiltermann%20confirms.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20if%20it%20links%20up%20with%20an%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20or%20even%20the%20mass%20expulsion%20of%20Pal